The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for weather recognition, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and recurrent neural networks (RNN), which are popular machine learning techniques used in computer vision and natural language processing, respectively. Therefore, the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and multimedia (cs.MM).
